The Distance Education program offers a home-study approach to learn robotics and automated systems. It requires only a personal computer and an Internet connection. The learning materials include 14 modules with various formats such as text, audio, 2D and 3D animations, computer-based testing, and RoboLogix simulation software. Open enrolment is available with no specific time limits to complete each module. Prerequisites include an Ontario Secondary School Diploma or equivalent or mature student status, but an electronics background is helpful but not essential. Career opportunities include installation, service, maintenance, troubleshooting and repair of robots and automated production systems, as well as working as a robotics trainer. The program consists of 14 required courses: ELNC 9101 - Introduction to Robotics; ELNC 9103 - Robot Classifications; ELNC 9108 - Manipulators and End Effectors; ELNC 9102 - Robot Drive Systems; ELNC 9106 - Servo Systems; ELNC 9105 - Payload, Repeatability and Accuracy; ELNC 9107 - Object Detection; ELNC 9112 - Vision, Touch and Sound; ELNC 9113 - Robot Programming; ELNC 9111 - Robot Safety; ELNC 9110 - Communications; ELNC 9109 - Applications; ELNC 9104 - Artificial Intelligence; and ELNC 9121 - Autonomous Robots.

The program is available on Apple computers running Mac Operating Systems, Chromebooks running Chrome Operating Systems, and devices running Linux Operating Systems.
